3. Select options (Can be changed at anytime)
CallerID Name Lookup
For Callers with a US/Canadian CallerID number, perform a lookup in the LIBD/CNAM database to find the name matching the number.

When activated, the system will display the result of this query in the CallerID name portion of the CallerID, leading to a "CallerID name" <5551231234> format when people call your number.

Please note that we will not charge for queries coming from a number matching an entry in your phone book.
DID POP
Set this to the server your software/device is registered to or receiving the call from. You can change this at any time.











Routing
Where to route the call for this DID.
Optional Failover Options  Click here to display









Routing if Destination Busy
Optionally, if the destination is busy, you can route calls to a specific destination.









Routing if Destination Unreachable
Optionally, if the destination is unreachable (Not registered, Network Issue, Power Outage etc.), you can route calls to a specific destination.









Routing if Destination No Answer
Optionally, if the destination does not answer the call, you can route calls to a specific destination.
Note:
Listed numbers are processed in real time and effective immediatly after your order.
'Carrier Order': we do not currently have any DIDs for that ratecenter in our pool. However it can be ordered directly with our carriers. If carrier has the rate center in stock, your number will be provisioned within 1 business day. If the DID is backorder, orders usually take 2-5 business days, but may take up to 30 business days to be completed depending on the ratecenter.
